Christ (4).” For saints in LA, the firm registration deadline to participate in this training by webcast is this Lord’s
Day, December 7 ($130). Sign up at <a href="https://tinyurl.com/wintertrainingla" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
	data-saferedirecturl="https://www.google.com/url?q=https://tinyurl.com/wintertrainingla&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1764775338359000&amp;usg=AOvVaw1989W6iEW6Gr-jww7gNgnS">tinyurl.com/wintertrainingla</a>.

Please pray for the release and receiving of the Lord’s speaking in this training. Such trainings are a precious
heritage in the Lord’s recovery. The purpose of these trainings is to minister the all-inclusive Christ as eternal life
embodied in the word of God to bring the believers to the full knowledge of the truth so that they may enjoy Christ as
life, grow in life unto maturity, and dispense life to others for the growth and building up of His Body.

May the Lord grant us to highly value the semiannual trainings and encourage others to have a heart for them, and may
the Lord grace us to bear the burden to pray for the trainings so that He as the seven Spirits of God may have an
unhindered way to continue to speak the present truth to the churches.
<h3>University Conference for Germany, Switzerland, Austria</h3>
The University Conference for students and young adults from Germany, Switzerland, Austria, and beyond is December 5 to
7. The saints will once again gather at Gut Elim to seek the Lord’s presence, sit at His feet, and listen to His Word
(Luke 10:39).

May the Lord grant each attendee mercy and grace (Heb. 4:16) to have a pure heart (Matt. 5:8) and be poor in spirit
(Matt. 5:3), so that they may receive freshly from the Lord what He wishes to say to this generation. May the Lord gain
many more young adults from these nations for the advancement of His move in Europe.
<h3>Brussels, Belgium</h3>
A conference will be held in Brussels, Belgium this weekend, December 6 to 7. Please pray for the release of the Lord’s
rich word to supply the saints and knit them together. Continue to pray for the strengthening of the Lord’s testimony in
this crucial city and for more saints to migrate there under the Head and in the Body.
<h3>Czech and Slovak Translation Work</h3>
The labor continues to translate the NT Recovery Version into the Czech and Slovak languages. It was a year ago when,
after thorough fellowship and many prayers, the translation team started their preparations for this project. This week,
the team finally begins the translation of the Gospel of Matthew. The translation of this book is expected to take until
June 2026. These first weeks and months are very crucial for the whole team of six translators, as they will still be
learning ways of working individually and corporately. It is also a new experience of applying everything they have
learned into practice, handling new translation tools, and establishing working procedures.

Please pray:
<ul>
	<li>For the Lord to be the team’s wisdom in setting the best principles for their work from the start.</li>
	<li>That the whole team be kept from unnecessary distractions to remain focused and on schedule.</li>
	<li>That the Lord Himself may become and remain the unique goal and focus of all the serving saints as they carry out
		their daily tasks.</li>
</ul>